me characteristic forenames:  Scandinavian Holger, Sten.","Swedish: ornamental name composed of an altered form of the placename element <i>vi</i> (representing either Old Norse <i>vithr</i> ‘forest’ or <i>vé</i> ‘sacred place’) + <i>man</i> ‘man’, or a habitational name for someone from a place called with the element <i>vi</i>.","English: variant of   Wyman  . This form of the surname is virtually non-existing in Britain."]},{"name":"Whyman","meanings":["English: variant of   Wyman  ."]},{"name":"Weimann","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Wilhelm, Kurt, Fritz, Hans, Helmuth, Juergen, Reinhold.","German:","variant of   Weinmann  ."]},{"name":"Wayment","meanings":["English: variant of <b>Waymont</b>, a variant of   Wyman  ."]},{"name":"Wayman","meanings":["English: variant of   Wyman   and   Waitman  .","Americanized form of German   Wehmann   and   Weidmann  ."]}]},{"name":"Francis","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["equivalent of Italian Francesco , originally a vocabulary word meaning ‘French’ or ‘Frenchman’ (Late Latin <i>Franciscus</i>;  compare  Frank  ). This was a nickname given to  St Francis  of Assisi (  1181–1226 ) because of his wealthy father's business connections with France. His baptismal name was  Giovanni . He had a pleasant, ordinary life as a child and young man, but after two serious illnesses, a period of military service, and a year as a prisoner of war in Perugia, he turned from the world and devoted himself to caring for the poor and sick. He was joined by groups of disciples, calling themselves ‘minor friars’ (<i>friari minores</i>). The main features of the Franciscan rule are humility, poverty, and love for all living creatures. The given name occurs occasionally in England as early as  1300 , and more frequently from the early 16th century, when there was a surge of admiration for, and imitation of, Italian Renaissance culture."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Francis Wyman was born in 1592. He had at least 1 son with Elizabeth Richardson. He died in 1658, at the age of 66."},"et":{"1592–1658":"1592–1658","1593–1630":"1593–1630","1619–1699":"1619–1699","1699":"1699","1630":"1630","1593":"1593","1592":"1592","1619":"1619","24 February 1619":"24. veebruar 1619","1658":"1658","Westmill, Hertfordshire, England":"Westmill, Hertfordshire, England"},"fi":{"1592–1658":"1592–1658","1593–1630":"1593–1630","1619–1699":"1619–1699","1699":"1699","1630":"1630","1593":"1593","1592":"1592","1619":"1619","24 February 1619":"24. helmikuuta 1619","1658":"1658","Westmill, Hertfordshire, England":"Westmill, Hertfordshire, England"},"fr":{"1592–1658":"1592–1658","1593–1630":"1593–1630","1619–1699":"1619–1699","1699":"1699","1630":"1630","1593":"1593","1592":"1592","1619":"1619","24 February 1619":"24 février 1619","1658":"1658","Westmill, Hertfordshire, England":"Westmill, Hertfordshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Francis Wyman est né en 1592. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Elizabeth Richardson. Il est décédé en 1658, à l’âge de 66 ans."},"de":{"1592–1658":"1592–1658","1593–1630":"1593–1630","1619–1699":"1619–1699","1699":"1699","1630":"1630","1593":"1593","1592":"1592","1619":"1619","24 February 1619":"24. Februar 1619","1658":"1658","Westmill, Hertfordshire, England":"Westmill, Hertfordshire, England","lifeSummary":"Francis Wyman wurde 1592 geboren. Er hatte mit Elizabeth Richardson mindestens 1 Sohn. Er starb 1658 im Alter von 66 Jahren."},"ht":{"1592–1658":"1592–1658","1593–1630":"1593–1630","1619–1699":"1619–1699","1699":"1699","1630":"1630","1593":"1593","1592":"1592","1619":"1619","24 February 1619":"24 February 1619","1658":"1658","Westmill, Hertfordshire, England":"Westmill, Hertfordshire, England"},"hu":{"1592–1658":"1592–1658","1593–1630":"1593–1630","1619–1699":"1619–1699","1699":"1699","1630":"1630","1593":"1593","1592":"1592","1619":"1619","24 February 1619":"1619. február 24.","1658":"1658","Westmill, H